<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Care Calendar - Period Support Guide</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Free period tracker for partners. Get personalized tips, track cycles, and learn how to provide the best support."/>
  <meta name="keywords" content="period tracker, menstrual cycle support, partner period guide"/>
  <meta property="og:title" content="Care Calendar - Period Support Guide for Partners"/>
  <meta property="og:description" content="Be the supportive partner she needs. Free period tracker with personalized tips for each phase of her cycle."/>
  <meta property="og:image" content="/images/care-calendar-social.jpg"/>
  <meta name="twitter:title" content="Care Calendar - Period Support Guide for Partners"/>
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="Be the supportive partner she needs. Free period tracker with personalized tips for each phase of her cycle."/>
  <meta name="twitter:image" content="/images/care-calendar-social.jpg"/>

  <link rel="canonical" href="https://downbad.cloud/care-calendar" />
  <link
    href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tailwindcss@2.2.19/dist/tailwind.min.css"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-100">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    
    <!-- Home Button -->
    <div class="flex justify-start mb-4">
      <a 
        href="https://www.downbad.cloud"
        class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-white bg-pink-600 rounded hover:bg-pink-700 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pink-600 focus:ring-offset-2"
      >
        Home
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Page Header / Title -->
    <header class="text-center mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-pink-600 mb-4">Care Calendar</h1>
      <p class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-gray-700">
        Being supportive starts with understanding. Track her cycle, learn her needs,
        and be there when it matters most. Made with ❤️ for caring partners, brothers,
        and fathers.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Tracker Section -->
    <section
      id="tracker-section"
      class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden"
    >
      <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-pink-600 mb-8 text-center">Support Tracker</h2>
        <p class="text-center text-gray-700 mb-8">
          Enter the first day of the last period and her usual cycle length. Once you click
          away or press Tab, the tracker updates automatically!
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Inputs Row -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2" for="lastPeriod">
                Last Period Start Date
              </label>
              <input
                type="date"
                id="lastPeriod"
                class="mt-1 p-2 border rounded w-full"
                placeholder="YYYY-MM-DD"
              />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2" for="cycleLength">
                Cycle Length (days)
              </label>
              <input
                type="number"
                id="cycleLength"
                value="28"
                min="21"
                max="35"
                class="mt-1 p-2 border rounded w-full"
              />
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase Info Display -->
          <div id="phaseInfo" class="mt-8">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg space-y-4">
              <!-- Current Phase and Dates -->
              <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-pink-800">
                Current Phase:
                <span id="phaseName" class="mr-2"></span>
              </h2>
              <p class="text-pink-600">
                <strong>Current Date:</strong>
                <span id="currentDate">Loading...</span>
              </p>
              <p class="text-pink-600">
                Next period expected: <span id="nextPeriod">N/A</span>
              </p>

              <!-- Tips / PartnerTips / Symptoms, stacked vertically -->
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-pink-700 mb-2">Partner Tips</h3>
                <ul id="partnerTips" class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600"></ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-pink-700 mb-2">Tips</h3>
                <ul id="tips" class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600"></ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-pink-700 mb-2">Common Symptoms</h3>
                <ul id="symptoms" class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600"></ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Educational Info Section -->
    <section id="educational-info" class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-12 text-gray-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pink-600 mb-6">Educational Info About Menstrual Cycles</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        The menstrual cycle is typically around 28 days, but can range from 21 to 35 days. Each phase
        involves different hormonal changes that can affect mood, energy, and the body overall.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
        <li>
          <strong>Menstrual Phase:</strong> Days 1–5 (approx). Uterus sheds its lining, leading to bleeding,
          cramps, low energy, and mood changes for many women.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Follicular Phase:</strong> After menstruation, the body prepares a new egg. Energy begins
          to increase, and mood often turns more upbeat.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ovulatory Phase:</strong> Around day 14 (in a 28-day cycle), the egg is released. This can
          be the peak of energy, sociability, and libido.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Luteal Phase:</strong> After ovulation, the body prepares for a possible pregnancy. Many
          experience PMS symptoms here, like moodiness or cravings.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4 font-semibold text-pink-600">
        Disclaimer: This guide is not a substitute for professional medical advice. If her pain or symptoms
        are severe, consult a healthcare professional.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Understanding these phases can help partners, fathers, brothers, and friends provide the right type
        of care—whether that’s extra rest, emotional support, or simply respecting her personal space.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        .
        &lt;3
        .
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Features Section (added here at the bottom in your final HTML, 
         but you can reorder as needed) -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10 p-6 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-pink-600 mb-4 text-center">Why Use Care Calendar?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 text-center">
        Tailored for caring partners, siblings, and supportive friends, this tracker is
        designed to make understanding a woman’s menstrual cycle easy and helpful.
        Discover key benefits below:
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="flex flex-col bg-pink-50 p-4 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-pink-800 mb-2">Understanding Is Caring</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            • Get unique tips for each phase of her cycle<br/>
            • Plan and adapt your support based on her mood &amp; energy<br/>
            • Strengthen emotional connection through empathy and awareness
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col bg-pink-50 p-4 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-pink-800 mb-2">Be Prepared</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            • Know when to restock on supplies or comfort items<br/>
            • Offer the right kind of support at the right time<br/>
            • Reduce surprise or last-minute stress
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col bg-pink-50 p-4 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-pink-800 mb-2">Simple to Use</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            • Enter the last period date and typical cycle length<br/>
            • The tracker automatically calculates her next period<br/>
            • Effortless design so you can focus on being supportive
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col bg-pink-50 p-4 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-pink-800 mb-2">Privacy First</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            • Data stored only in your browser<br/>
            • No unnecessary signups or personal data collection<br/>
            • Fully respects her right to confidentiality and trust
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 px-2">
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-center">
          Caring is a journey. By learning to recognize her changing needs, you’re showing
          genuine empathy. If uncertainty arises, always communicate openly and encourage
          professional healthcare support for any unusual symptoms.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pink-600 mb-6">Common Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800">Why should I track her cycle?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Understanding her cycle helps you provide better emotional and physical support
            when she needs it most.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800">How accurate is this tracker?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            While every woman's cycle is unique, this tool provides general guidance based on
            typical cycle patterns.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800">Is it okay to track someone else's cycle?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Always get consent and maintain open communication. This tool is meant to enhance
            understanding and support, never to invade privacy.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="text-center mt-12 py-4 text-gray-600">
      <p>Made with care for those who care. Share with other supportive partners.</p>
    </footer>
  </div>

  <!-- JavaScript Reference -->
  <script src="/care-calender/script.js" defer></script>
  <script>
    /*
      Displays the current date in #currentDate. If you've already done this in script.js,
      you can remove this snippet.
    */
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
      const currentDateEl = document.getElementById("currentDate");
      if (currentDateEl) {
        const now = new Date();
        currentDateEl.textContent = now.toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
          weekday: "long",
          year: "numeric",
          month: "long",
          day: "numeric",
        });
      }
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>